Ronda Blaylock was just 14-years-old when she and a friend took a ride home from Atkins High School in Rural Hall, North Carolina .
Three days later, her partially clothed body was found in a heavily wooded area 20 miles away .
The man who gave her ride home was never found .
Surry County Sheriff Graham Atkinson said in a press conference on Monday the man still lives in the area and they are close to getting him arrested .